path returned by \code{.eb_raw_q_values()} (the Walters replication contract
used by the package's FDR tests). An internal monotone-correction helper
\code{.eb_monotone_q_values()} is available for diagnostic comparison but is NOT
substituted into the returned \code{q_values}.

When \code{method = "both"}, the returned \code{selected} indicator follows the top
\code{selection_share} units by smallest q-values. This makes \code{"both"} most
useful for like-for-like decision-frontier comparison rather than ordinary
FDR thresholding. The KRW race fixture under default
\code{pi0_method = "storey"} yields the published \eqn{\hat\pi_0 \approx 0.39}
and 27-firm selection at \eqn{\alpha = 0.05} (CD-78 anchor).

If \code{posterior} is omitted but posterior-mean classification or a frontier
is needed, the function computes the posterior internally via \code{\link[=eb_shrink]{eb_shrink()}}
with \code{method = "nonparametric"}.
