\section{Decision tree -- which method}{

\itemize{
\item \code{method = "qvalue"} -- when you want FDR-controlled selection at \eqn{\alpha} level.
\item \code{method = "posterior_mean"} -- when you want a deterministic top-share / threshold by posterior mean.
\item \code{method = "both"} -- both rules computed; \code{selected} follows the top \code{selection_share} by q-value (decision-frontier comparison, not ordinary FDR thresholding).
